5 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
6 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
7 Article – Natural Resources
8 10–206.
9 (A) The Department may reduce the wildlife population in any county, election
10 district, or other identifiable area of the State after a thorough investigation reveals that
11 protected wildlife is seriously injurious to agricultural or other interests in the affected
12 area. The method of reducing the wildlife population is at the Department’s discretion,
13 except that trapping is preferred whenever feasible. The Department shall dispose of
14 wildlife taken pursuant to the provisions of this section as the Department deems
15 advisable.
16 (B) (1) IN THIS SUBSECTION, “DEER DAMAGE” INCLUDES:
17 (I) WIDESPREAD DAMAGE CAUSED BY DEER, INCLUDING THE
18 ELIMINATION OF FOREST UNDERSTORY, TREE REGENERATION, AND NATIVE
19 PLANTS; AND
20 (II) THE DESTRUCTION OF AGRICULTURAL CROPS OR
21 LANDSCAPING, INCLUDING ORNAMENTAL LANDSCAPING, CAUSED BY DEER.
22 (2) THE DEPARTMENT MAY AUTHORIZE THE REDUCTION OF THE
23 DEER POPULATION ON ANY SINGLE, CONTIGUOUS PROPERTY OF AT LEAST 10 ACRES
24 WHERE THE DEPARTMENT HAS DOCUMENTED DEER DAMAGE.
25 (3) (I) THE METHOD OF REDUCING THE DEER POPULATION:
26 1. IS AT THE DEPARTMENT’S DISCRETION; AND
27 2. SUBJECT TO SUBPARAGRAPH (II) OF THIS
28 PARAGRAPH, MAY INCLUDE THE ISSUANCE OF A PERMIT TO A PROPERTY OWNER, OR
29 THE PROPERTY OWNER’S EMPLOYEE, LESSEE, OR AGENT, TO SHOOT DEER ON THE
30 PROPERTY ON SUNDAYS.
31 (II) A PERMIT ISSUED UNDER SUBPARAGRAPH (I)2 OF THIS
32 PARAGRAPH SHALL PROHIBIT DEER HUNTING ON SUNDAYS DURING DEER
33 FIREARMS SEASON WITHIN 25 150 YARDS OF A DEPARTMENT TRAIL DESIGNATED

